          "type": "MACRO_BLOCK",
          "content": ".TH",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " INTRO 2 2017-09-15 \"Linux\" \"Linux Programmer's Manual\""
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "macro",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_BLOCK",
          "content": ".SH",
          "translatable": true
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " NAME"
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "content",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "intro "
        },
        {
          "type": "ESCAPE",
          "content": "\\-"
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " introduction to system calls"
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "macro",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_BLOCK",
          "content": ".SH",
          "translatable": true
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " DESCRIPTION"
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "content",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "Section 2 of the manual describes the Linux system calls."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "A system call is an entry point into the Linux kernel."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "Usually, system calls are not invoked directly:"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "instead, most system calls have corresponding C library"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "wrapper functions which perform the steps required"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "(e.g., trapping to kernel mode) in order to invoke"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "the system call."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "Thus, making a system call looks the same as invoking a normal"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "library function."
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "macro",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_BLOCK",
          "content": ".PP",
          "translatable": false
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "content",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "In many cases, the C library wrapper function does nothing more than:"
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "macro",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_BLOCK",
          "content": ".IP",
          "translatable": true
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " * 3"
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "content",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "copying arguments and the unique system call number to the"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "registers where the kernel expects them;"
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "macro",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_BLOCK",
          "content": ".IP",
          "translatable": true
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " *"
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "content",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "trapping to kernel mode,"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "at which point the kernel does the real work of the system call;"
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "macro",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_BLOCK",
          "content": ".IP",
          "translatable": true
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " *"
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "content",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "setting"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".I",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " errno"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "if the system call returns an error number when the kernel returns the"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "CPU to user mode."
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "macro",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_BLOCK",
          "content": ".PP",
          "translatable": false
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "content",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "However, in a few cases, a wrapper function may do rather more than this,"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "for example, performing some preprocessing"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "of the arguments before trapping to kernel mode,"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "or postprocessing of values returned by the system call."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "Where this is the case, the manual pages in Section 2 generally"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "try to note the details of both the (usually GNU) C library API"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "interface and the raw system call."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "Most commonly, the main DESCRIPTION will focus on the C library interface,"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "and differences for the system call are covered in the NOTES section."
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "macro",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_BLOCK",
          "content": ".PP",
          "translatable": false
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "content",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "For a list of the Linux system calls, see"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " syscalls (2)."
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "macro",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_BLOCK",
          "content": ".SH",
          "translatable": true
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " RETURN VALUE"
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "content",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "On error, most system calls return a negative error number"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "(i.e., the negated value of one of the constants described in"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " errno (3))."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "The C library wrapper hides this detail from the caller: when a"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "system call returns a negative value, the wrapper copies the"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "absolute value into the"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".I",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " errno"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "variable, and returns "
        },
        {
          "type": "ESCAPE",
          "content": "\\-"
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "1 as the return value of the wrapper."
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "macro",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_BLOCK",
          "content": ".PP",
          "translatable": false
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "content",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "The value returned by a successful system call depends on the call."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "Many system calls return 0 on success, but some can return nonzero"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "values from a successful call."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "The details are described in the individual manual pages."
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "macro",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_BLOCK",
          "content": ".PP",
          "translatable": false
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "content",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "In some cases,"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "the programmer must define a feature test macro in order to obtain"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "the declaration of a system call from the header file specified"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "in the man page SYNOPSIS section."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "(Where required, these feature test macros must be defined before including"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".I",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " any"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "header files.)"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "In such cases, the required macro is described in the man page."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "For further information on feature test macros, see"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " feature_test_macros (7)."
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "macro",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_BLOCK",
          "content": ".SH",
          "translatable": true
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " CONFORMING TO"
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "content",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "Certain terms and abbreviations are used to indicate UNIX variants"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "and standards to which calls in this section conform."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "See"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " standards (7)."
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "macro",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_BLOCK",
          "content": ".SH",
          "translatable": true
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " NOTES"
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "macro",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_BLOCK",
          "content": ".SS",
          "translatable": true
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " Calling directly"
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "content",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "In most cases, it is unnecessary to invoke a system call directly,"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "but there are times when the Standard C library does not implement"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "a nice wrapper function for you."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "In this case, the programmer must manually invoke the system call using"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " syscall (2)."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "Historically, this was also possible using one of the _syscall macros"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "described in"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " _syscall (2)."
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "macro",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_BLOCK",
          "content": ".SS",
          "translatable": true
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " Authors and copyright conditions"
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "content",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "Look at the header of the manual page source for the author(s) and copyright"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "conditions."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "Note that these can be different from page to page!"
